  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2023-04-20",
    "date": "2023-05-04T15:31:24Z",
    "text": "Prevent Family Fire Act of 2023 \n\nThis bill allows through 2030 a new tax credit equal to 10% of amounts received from the first retail sale of a safe firearm storage device, not to exceed $400 per device.\n\nThe bill defines safe firearm storage device as a device that is designed and marketed to deny unauthorized access to, or render inoperable, a firearm or ammunition, and is secured by a combination lock, key lock, or lock based on biometric information."
  },
